  "gloss": "For rich readout classes, every continuous target on a compact domain can be approximated to any desired accuracy by an explicitly constructed ReLU network. This is the rigid side of the dichotomy, where approximation is total.\n\n**Cites** `ZPM.ReLU.relu_uat` — the corpus theorem this result restates and discharges.\n\n**Original contribution.** The raw lemma is a ReLU universal-approximation theorem; the thesis-layer statement positions it as the 'rigid half' of a dichotomy — the closure-rich case where the geometry is fully approximable.\n",
